Privacy Policy for Centrist and Affiliated Apps and Websites
Effective Date:
October 10, 2024
1. Introduction
Welcome to
AllCentrist APPS
, developed by
AllCentrist Developers
(“we,” “us,” or “our”). Your privacy is paramount to us, and we are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our mobile application (“App”) and any affiliated services.
By accessing or using our App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not use our App.
2. Information We Collect
2.1. Personal Information
Account Information:
When you create an account, we collect your email address and password. If you sign in using third-party services like Google Sign-In, we may collect additional information such as your name and profile picture.
Profile Information:
Information you provide when updating your profile, including username, profile picture, and bio.
2.2. Location Data
Precise Location:
We collect precise location data (latitude and longitude) when you use location-based features within the App.
Background Location:
With your consent, we may access your location even when the App is not in use to provide continuous location-based services.
2.3. Media Access
Camera Access:
To capture photos and videos for your posts.
Photo Library Access:
To upload and analyze images and videos.
Microphone Access:
To record audio in videos.
2.4. File Access
Files:
Access to your device’s storage to upload and analyze media files.
2.5. Apple Music Access
Music Library:
Access to your Apple Music library to select audio files for upload and analysis.
2.6. Device and Usage Information
Device Information:
Information about your device, including hardware model, operating system version, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.
Usage Data:
Details of your interactions with the App, such as feature usage, navigation, and in-app actions.
Analytics Data:
Information collected through Firebase Analytics to understand user behavior and improve the App.
2.7. Communication Data
FCM Tokens:
Firebase Cloud Messaging tokens used to send push notifications to your device.
2.8. Ad Data
Advertising Identifiers:
Used for personalized advertising through Google Mobile Ads SDK and other advertising partners.
3. How We Use Your Information
3.1. Provide and Improve Services
Service Delivery:
To operate and maintain the App, including location-based services, media uploads, and social networking features.
Personalization:
To personalize your experience by recommending content, connecting you with friends, and tailoring ads based on your preferences and behavior.
Feature Enhancement:
To develop new features and improve existing functionalities based on user feedback and usage patterns.
3.2. Communication
Notifications:
To send you push notifications about updates, offers, and important information related to the App.
Customer Support:
To respond to your inquiries, provide support, and resolve issues you encounter while using the App.
Marketing:
To send promotional materials, newsletters, and marketing communications with your consent.
3.3. Analytics and Research
Data Analysis:
To analyze usage trends, user interactions, and other data to enhance the App’s performance and user experience.
Research:
To conduct research and analysis to understand user needs and preferences better.
3.4. Advertising
Personalized Ads:
To deliver personalized advertisements based on your interests and interactions within the App.
Ad Performance:
To measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns and improve ad targeting.
4. How We Share Your Information
4.1. Service Providers
We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as:
Firebase:
For analytics, authentication, cloud messaging, and database services.
Google Maps:
For location-based services and mapping functionalities.
Google Mobile Ads:
For delivering personalized advertisements.
Apple Music:
To access your music library for specific features.
4.2. Advertising Partners
We share anonymized and aggregated data with advertising partners to deliver personalized ads and measure ad performance.
4.3. Legal Requirements
We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities, such as a court or government agency.
4.4. Business Transfers
In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred to the acquiring entity.
4.5. Affiliates
We may share your information with our affiliated companies to provide you with enhanced services and features.
5. Your Rights and Choices
5.1. Access and Correction
You have the right to access, update, or correct your personal information by logging into your account and modifying your profile settings.
5.2. Data Deletion
You can request the deletion of your personal information by contacting us at
roameo@allcentrist.com
. Please note that we may retain certain information as required by law or for legitimate business purposes.
5.3. Opt-Out
Analytics and Advertising:
You can opt out of receiving personalized ads by adjusting your device settings or through
Google’s Ads Settings
.
Push Notifications:
You can disable push notifications in your device settings if you no longer wish to receive them.
5.4. Consent Withdrawal
You can withdraw your consent for data collection at any time by disabling the relevant permissions in your device settings or by contacting us at
roameo@allcentrist.com
. Withdrawing consent may limit your ability to use certain features of the App.
6. Data Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include encryption, secure servers, and regular security assessments. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
7. Children’s Privacy
Our App is intended for users who are at least 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal information from a child under 13, we will delete such information promptly.
8. Third-Party Links
Our App may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not operated by us. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these third parties. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any changes by updating the “Effective Date” at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates.
10. Contact Us
